Guide: OOP GUI Creation

Steps
- Begin with `#Requires AutoHotkey v2` and instantiate your GUI class without `new`.
- Store the Gui object as a property for access across methods.
- Bind events with `.Bind(this)` to preserve context.
- Provide methods like `Toggle` or `Show` for visibility management.
- Release resources in `__Delete` when the GUI persists.

Example
```cpp
#Requires AutoHotkey v2
#SingleInstance Force
DemoGui()

class DemoGui {
    __New() {
        this.gui := Gui("+Resize", "Demo")
        this.gui.AddText("w200", "Name")
        this.gui.AddEdit("vName w200")
        this.gui.AddButton("Default w200", "Submit").OnEvent("Click", this.Submit.Bind(this))
    }
    Submit(*) {
        data := this.gui.Submit()
        MsgBox(data.Name)
        this.gui.Hide()
    }
    Toggle(*) {
        if WinExist("ahk_id " this.gui.Hwnd)
            this.gui.Hide()
        else
            this.gui.Show()
    }
}
```

Edge Cases
- Missing event bindings leading to unresponsive controls.
- Uninitialized control variables causing errors.
- Multiple instantiations creating duplicate GUIs.

